To butterfly shrimp, slice down back of shrimp with small sharp knife, almost completely through. Spread and flatten to form butterfly shape. Combine olive oil, vinegar, lemon juice, basil, parsley, oregano and red pepper flakes in shallow bowl. Add shrimp; toss to coat. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes. Remove shrimp from marinade, discarding marinade. Grill or broil shrimp, turning once, until shrimp turn pink. Spoon sauce over hot farfalle and top with shrimp. Garnish, if desired, with additional parsley.